==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{rhymes|ɪfi}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|jiffies}}

# {{context|colloquial|lang=en}} A very short, unspecified length of time.
#: ''I'll be back in a '''jiffy'''.''
# {{context|computing|lang=en}} A unit of time defined by the frequency of its basic timer; historically, and by convention, 0.01 seconds, but some operating systems use other values.
# {{context|electronics|lang=en}} The time between [[alternating current]] power cycles (1/60 or 1/50 of a second)
# {{context|physics|lang=en}} The time taken for light to travel one centimetre in a vacuum (sometimes one foot, or sometimes the width of a [[nucleon]])

